A '''meteorite mineral''' is a mineral found chiefly or exclusively within [[meteorite]]s or meteorite derived material. This is a list of those minerals, excluding minerals also commonly found in terrestrial rocks. As of 1997 there were approximately 295 mineral species which have been identified in meteorites.<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1111/j.1945-5100.1997.tb01558.x |title=Mineralogy of meteorite groups - an update |first=Alan E.|last=Rubin |journal=Meteoritics |volume=32 |pages=733–734 |date=Sep 1997 |bibcode=1997M&PS...32..733R |issue=5}}</ref>
